Key Match Events: Jalen Brunson expressed displeasure with the Knicks' performance on both offense and defense in their 109-97 loss to the Houston Rockets.
The Knicks shot 39 percent from the floor and had 20 assists in the game.
The Knicks were outrebounded 50-39 by the Rockets.
Tyler Kolek was the only Knicks bench player to score, contributing three points.
Jalen Brunson scored 29 points and had eight assists on 9-24 shooting.
Post-Match Reflections: Jalen Brunson emphasized the need for the Knicks to improve their defensive stops and offensive switching.
